I luckily have a great doorman who keeps a log of everyone that comes to the building, and I repeatedly told Klom Klorm this, but they would not budge. Finally, I asked to speak with the ownership because this was legitimate thievery at this point. I had paid and tipped well on my food. Checked the place out last night after wishing and hoping a thai place would open in the hood for YEARS. This restaurant mostly doesn't disappoint. I ordered the corn appetizer, shrimp pad thai and shrimp pad see ew. The appetizer was the big weak spot of the meal - it was a small portion of grilled corn on the cob sitting in a small puddle of watery coconut milk. The corn was not very flavorful and had terrible texture.. I get that corn isn't in season now, but maybe they shouldn't offer this until late summer then? The rest of the food was very good - though I wish the shrimp had been de-shelled as it's very messy to do it yourself while eating. One other thing I noticed- there aren't enough bar stools/chairs so they can't seat as many people as they should. Honestly I'd really give the place 3 1/2 stars but I think they have a little fine tuning to do.
A must visit Thai restaurant this  side of #Brooklyn
